sh invariants from variants\r\n3. Makes predictions about next pulse content\r\n4. Validates against success criteria\r\n\r\nThis is specific, file-based, and advances the Phase 1 advancement goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a concrete hypothesis to test: if I can classify pulse content as invariant vs variant and predict next pulse content, I validate that causal discovery and compression are the same problem. The TIC experiment is the most actionable next step.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that reads recent pulse logs, identifies invariant vs variant patterns, and tests against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 23:59:27\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774325143887}}
